      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLAZING EMERALD (2) hasn't won for a while, but put the writing on the wall last start when 1.4L off the winner over the mile in Saturday grade. The form out of that race has been solid and while she comes back in grade, she has placed 3/5 here. Drawn inside with a claim and can make an impression. SATURDAY SESH (3) should sit handy from a favourable alley and has been good in stronger company recently. Back to midweek company now  and while he does rise in weight, he'll be in this for a very long way. TRIBAL RULER (9) flew home from the back to win as a 40-1 chance fresh, winning impressively. Up in trip is a good move and this looks to shape similarly. He remains down in the weights and if he can run up to the fresh performance, he'll be in the finish once again. I'M NIPOTE (5) flew home impressively first-up and won't be far away once again. CAPORETTO (7) is racing in good order and can be thereabouts once more.",
